CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1783941694
OL,3,CMore than 200 'troublemakers'
OL,4,Cdispersed as police tackle anti-social
OL,5,Cbehaviour
OL,7,FBetween 1 May and 1 July 2026,
OL,8,Fofficers recorded 219 dispersal
OL,9,Fnotices, telling people to either
OL,10,Fleave an area or face arrest if they
OL,11,Frefused or returned later.
OL,13,FKent Police says it will also seize
OL,14,Fitems like loud speakers if they are
OL,15,Fbeing used antisocially.
OL,17,FThe force is also working with British
OL,18,FTransport Police, Southeastern and
OL,19,FNetwork Rail to try and tackle
OL,20,Fnuisance behaviour on trains and at
OL,21,Ftrain stations over the summer.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
